8:
Yes. Soft and supple as a newborn
baby.
33: So soft! I'm so soft, Stella!
43:
Paradise Isle... What other secrets do
you hold?
46: Now, what shall we do next?
50:
Next we will explore more... adult
entertainment.
60:
Oh my... The lights... The sounds... It's
almost overwhelming...
63:
Can't take a trip to Paradise Isle
without stopping by the casino.
We're regulars here.
68:
Yeah, a regular thorn in their side...
You sure it's okay for us to be here?
72:
They said not to worry about it,
didn't they? Don't be such a party
pooper.
77:
Are you sure such an establishment
is... suitable for Princess Lilith?
81:
You needn't worry, Light. I'm well
aware gambling exists on all
manner of worlds, along with the
thrills that accompany it.
84:
Such games are fine in moderation.
You simply need to know when to
quit. Now then, let's give this a shot!
89: Come on, red! Thirty-two red! Re—
108:
Next time will be thirty-two red. I
know it!
113:
How?! And why are you fixated on
that number?! If you're looking for a
sign to stop, THIS IS IT!
117:
But I believe in the flames of
courage!
119:
Those flames are about to burn a
hole in your wallet!
125:
Alk, you remind me an awful lot of
how Shakari used to be.
128:
I wish I could be reckless too, and
have something to show for it...
132:
I mean... This isn't exactly the place
to be reckless, you know?
136:
That's... a fair point. Although I think I
was in too deep to quit...
140:
I see now that casinos are indeed
dens of evil. I'll have to forbid such
institutions in my country.
143:
Hehe. That's funny coming from
someone who is so clearly enjoying
our establishment.
149:
I am Esmeralda, the manager of this
"den of evil."
153:
The manager... M-my apologies!
Please forgive my crude outburst.
156:
You have nothing to be sorry for.
Bars are for wallowing in your
sorrows as you drink your problems
away.
157:
You folks seem like you'd make fine
patrons of our casino, so before you
completely dismiss our
establishment, I'd like to explain one
thing.
158:
Casino Belaqua is a place of
ambition—of seizing the day for all it
is worth.
163:
All of us here are reaching for far-off
dreams. Such dreams are what
made this island what it is today.
164:
Did you know this island was once a
mountain that jutted out of the
ocean?
166:
A mountain? But I thought this island
was man-made...
168:
That it is. People crushed the
mountain and made it into this
island's foundation.
170:
This was back when the water levels
were still rising, and everyone was
always on the lookout for higher
ground. I'm sure that such an
undertaking seemed impossible at
the time.
171:
But they never gave up on their
dream and built a life here. And it's
those kinds of dreams that draw
people to this casino.
174:
...Could you tell me more about this
island's history?
176: Oho... I see a new spark in your eyes.
179:
You'll have to forgive me. While I
mean no offense, I happen to find
such stories far more interesting
than cards or roulette.
183: Lilith looks like she's having fun.
185:
...Is this also a form of adult
entertainment?
189: Uh... I don't know if I'd call it that, but...
193:
That look in Lilith's eyes is the same
as the look she had when she stood
before Adjudicus that one time.
200:
What a fascinating story. Could you
tell me more?
